Know more about National Bank of Pakistan NBP

National Bank of Pakistan (NBP) is a government-owned multinational commercial bank of Pakistan with international presence in the US, UK, Canada, Germany, Saudi Arabia, China, Bangladesh, Afghanistan, and many other countries. A subsidiary of the State Bank of Pakistan (SBP), NBP operates over 1,500 branches nationwide and has assets that are worth over $20 billion.

The bank is headquartered in Karachi and offers commercial as well as public sector banking services. NBP’s wide range of consumer products caters to all income segments of the population and also includes Shariah Compliant Islamic Banking products and remittance service for overseas Pakistanis. The bank also has a string CSR footprint in the country.
